result.execSummary:
The defendant Rexford A. Zemialkowski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent to count 2 but consecutive to any other sentence with zero days credit. Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program. Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program after 3 years of confinement.

superMiscConds.notes: Restitution to be determined by the District Attorney within 30 days or deemed waived, any objections to be filed within 10 days of notice of determination.

If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. Clerk of Courts shall docket without fees. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

No use or possession of controlled substances, unless prescribed by a physician. No possession of drug paraphernalia. No intoxicants. Maintain Absolute Sobriety. No contact with victim or co-defendant and no contact through third party.

Complete compas assessment, counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments as appropriate and followup.  Pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections. Submit DNA sample if not previously submitted.  Defendant shall Submit to Random Urinalysis.
